An Igbo youth organization, Federated Igbo Youths Amalgamated, has called on Abia State Governor, Okezie Ikpeazu, to consider assisting a Peoples Democratic Party aspirant, Dr. Sampson Orji, to become the next state governor, come 2023. Arising from their zonal meeting Monday, the youths said the PDP aspirant has all it takes to take the state higher and “possesses enormous capacity to establish Abia State of our collective dreams for a prosperous, positive and forward-looking state”. Addressing newsmen after the meeting in Umuahia, the president of the group, Steven Eke, said “time has come for the enthronement of a responsible, responsive, quality, effective, efficient and sustainable development and growth targeted administration in Abia State. “The Man we want and the Governor Abia State Needs in 2023 will stand in the gap for all of us. “He will create multiple value chains that will lead to the reengineering of our Economic fiber that will locate Abia State first among the committee of states in the country. He is the man that will bring about generational change”. He said, “as the governor, Sampson Orji (SCORJ) will ensure that the entire Abia State landscape is captured in the Security Mapping Network to ensure a safe society for the state. “In all good conscience, what else can we do than to urge this man of glaring reckoning of human actions to take his good works further in service to the people of Abia State and make things happen again.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com